Iterator<String> iterate = windowsid.iterator();

    System.out.println(iterate.next());
}

<<<explanation>>>: The issue is that you are calling `iterate.next()` twice before checking if there is a next element with `iterate.hasNext()`. This causes a `NoSuchElementException` when there are no more elements in the iterator. To fix this, move the `iterate.next()` calls inside the loop after checking if there is a next element.
